 Chinas Liu offers a revision to current understandings of what queer theory is, does, and can be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChinese fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHomosexualityxPolitical aspectszChina. 0aPhilosophy, MarxistzChina. 0aQueer theoryzChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822375081?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822375081423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822375081/original  a978-3-11-071182-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles